Chandrakala gets the name from the shape. Chandrakala is chandran means moon, so its half-moon shape.

info.description: Serves 1 | Hot & crispy khasta with spicy potatoes and matar, along side lemon, green chilies, waxed onions, which may be mouth watering on sight.

info.name: Dal Vada with Aloo & Matar
info.description: Serves 1 | Dal vada also known as masala vada are savory, spiced, crunchy fritters that are a popular street food in south india. Gluten-free and vegan. But in the city of nawabs it | | served with matar & two types of potatoes, garnished with fried green chilly, onion & nimbu along with red/green chutney.

info.name: Poori with Aloo & Matar
info.description: Serves 1 | Poori is a deep fried, puffed bread, quite popular in northern india. This crisp, flaky texture poori makes a great accompaniment to many indian dishes. Typically, this poori is served with some matar curry and two types of potatos with garnishing of onion,fried chilly,nimbu and pudina with red/green chutney.

info.name: Chola Bhatura (Paneer Stuffed)
info.description: Serves 1 | Chole bhature is a food dish popular in the northern areas of the indian subcontinent. It is a combination of chana masala and bhatura/puri, a fried bread made from maida with stuffing of paneer. Although it is known as a typical punjabi dish | Chef's Special |

info.name: Chole Pulao
info.description: Serves 1 | Chole pulao is a one-pot spiced, fragrant and delish chickpea rice or chickpea pilaf made with fragrant basmati rice, melt in the mouth white chickpeas (garbanzo beans), sharp onions, tangy tomatoes, healthy herbs and bold spices. This indian chickpea rice makes for a filling, comforting and satisfying meal accompanied with a side of vegetable salad, yogurt dip or raita or plain yogurt.

info.name: Samosa With Chutney
info.description: Serves 1 | You don't need an occasion to enjoy a yummy, hot and crispy samosa.

info.name: Samosa With Chole And Chutney
info.description: Serves 1 | It's a meal of chole and 1 pc samosa served with salad and chutney...

info.name: Dhokla With Chutney
info.description: Dhokla is a steamed savory cake made with fermented batter of lentils and rice which is good for health. The batter is steamed to a cake in a mould. It is then topped with a tempering made of spices and curry leaves. Lastly dhokla is garnished with coconut, sesame seeds and coriander leaves along with green chutney.

info.name: Poha
info.description: Serves 1 | The indori poha has a characteristic of healthy meal for fitness freaks & it is sweet-sour in taste, and is often enjoyed with jalebi. Poha is flattened rice that is steam cooked with onions, spices and herbs...

info.name: Fried Idli With Chutney
info.description: Serves 1 | Fried idli is a soft, fluffy & spicy steamed cake made of fermented rice & lentil batter and garnished with chat masala and little spices. These are one of the healthiest protein packed breakfasts from south indian cuisine. Idli are easily digestible as the rice & lentils known as dal are soaked, ground, fermented & then prepared by steaming the batter. These are served with a green chutney

info.description: Serves 1 | Methi thepla is a flavoured flat bread from gujarati cuisine prepared with fresh fenugreek leaves.these leaves are slightly bitter with a hint of maple, and smell fantastic both raw and when cooked. It is typically served for breakfast and lunch with plain yogurt and mango pickle

info.name: Jalebi (Desi Ghee)
info.description: Jalebi, a spiral shaped crunchy sweet dipped in saffron laced sugar syrup, is the most popular traditional indian sweet...

info.name: Imarti (Desi Ghee)
info.description: Imarti or amrita is a sweet from India. It is made by deep-frying vina mungo flour batter in a circular flower shape, then soaking in sugar syrup... In the city of nawabs people like to have this dessert with rabri to add more deliciousness in their taste...

info.description: Flaky and tasty kachori made with spiced urad dal stuffing.

info.name: Khasta Karari Kachori With Aloo & Matar
info.description: Karare khaste are flaky as well as crunchy in the texture. These kachori's are fried in slow frying on a low heat. The oil has to be at a low or low-medium to make the crust of kachori crunchy...

info.name: Maida Puri With Aloo & Matar
info.description: Poori is a deep fried, puffed bread of maida, quite popular in northern india. This crisp, flaky texture poori makes a great accompaniment to many indian dishes. Typically, this poori is served with some matar curry and two types of potatoes with garnishing of onion,fried chilli,nimbu and pudina with red/green chutney...

info.name: Karare Vada With Aloo & Matar
info.description: Super crunchy masala vada prepared by deep frying in small pieces in low heat to make a crispy snacK.

info.name: Sponge (Rasgulla)
info.description: Serves 1 | Rasgulla, also known in rosogolla is a south asian syrupy dessert popular in the indian regions with south asian diaspora. It is made from ball-shaped dumplings of chhena and semolina dough, cooked in light sugar syrup made of sugar... | Seasonal | Chef's Special |

info.name: Ras Malai
info.description: Serves 1 | Rasmalai is yet another one of everyones favorite sweet. This bengali specialty is made with rasgulla (sweetened balls of paneer) soaked in sweetened, thickened milk that has been scented with cardamom and saffron. The result is a creamy, dreamy dessert that absolutely melts in your mouth.

info.name: Rabri 100 Gm
info.description: Serves 1 | Rabri is a sweet, condensed-milk-based dish, made by boiling milk on low heat for a long time until it becomes dense and changes its colour to off-white or pale yellow. Jaggery, spices, and nuts are added to it to give it flavor. It is chilled and served as dessert.

info.name: Gulab Jamun
info.description: Gulab jamun is an indian dessert of fried dough balls that are soaked in a sweet, sticky sugar syrup. As per tradition, the syrup has a delicate rose flavour: gulab means 'rose water' and jamun refers to a berry of a similar size and colour...

info.name: Kala Jamun
info.description: Serves 1 | Classic kala jamun made with khoya (dried milk solids). These small deep fried balls are stuffed with dry fruits & soaked in a sugar syrup flavored with rose water, cardamom and saffron.

info.name: Chena Sandwich (Piece)
info.description: Chena sandwich is a famous bengali sweet-dish recipe made from milk, paneer and khoya in the shape of sandwich. This easy dessert recipe is popular during festivals like durga puja and rakshabandhan.

info.name: Raj Bhog
info.description: Serves 1 | Rajbhog is also known as 'kesar rasgulla'. This classic bengali sweet prepared with milk solids and kesar strands. The texture and pattern of rajbhog sweet are more or less similar to rasgulla recipe, with a major difference in colour and dry fruits stuffing.

info.name: Mal Pua (Piece)
info.description: Malpua is a traditional north indian sweet of sugar syrup coated pancakes made with all-purpose flour, curd (yogurt), spices, khoya (dried milk solids) and topped with nuts. Malpua is often made during festivals, special occasions and are a street food as well. Soft and fluffy on the inside, yet crisp and lacy on the outside, these syrup dipped pancakes are a real treat ??especially when you serve them with rabri!

info.name: Mango Katori
info.description: Serves 1 | This mango kheer is a chena kheer meets mango version and has everything you love about the mango kheer. The elachi n saffron flavor, the perfectly soaked and thick n creamy milk. It is rich, smooth and naturally creamy. And when you serve it cold, it becomes one of those dessert everyone would really love to have on a perfectly hot summer day. To me it might even score more than an ice cream...

info.name: Chandra Kala (Piece)
info.description: Serves 1 | Chandrakala is a dessert from bihar, similar to gujia. The outer covering is made of flour and the stuffing is traditionally made using dry fruits like raisins, coconut, almonds, and cashews, along with khoa, semolina, cardamom, sugar, and pistachio. Chandrakala gets the name from the shape. Chandrakala is chandran means moon, so its half-moon shape.

info.name: Mini Rasgulla (Raspberry 100 Gm)
info.description: Mini rasgulla "juicy, fluffy, soft dumplings of chenna (fresh curd cheese) soaked in pistachios flavored sweet syrup. Dig into this indulgent goodness with our rasgulla bowl and treat yourself to the most authentic bengali experience. "

info.name: Kela Bhog (Pyali)
info.description: Serves 1 | It's a rattilal's special sweet paradise "kela bhog". Kela bhog is a smooth, thick mixture made of caramelized milk and sugar, garnished with pomegranate, almond & pistachio used as a flavoring, spread, or dessert topping.

info.name: Cham Cham (Piece)
info.description: Serves 1 | Cham cham is a traditional bengali sweet, popular throughout south asia. The sweet comes in a variety of colors, mainly light orange, light yellow, and white. It is coated with coconut or mawa flakes as a garnish.

info.name: Malai Roll
info.description: Serves 1 | Malai roll is an indian sweet where chena slices are stuffed with a rich and flavorful stuffing of milk fudge along with dry fruits and then dunked in thin reduced milk...

info.name: Laung Lata (Piece)
info.description: Serves 1 | Laung lata is a bengali dish that is made specially on festivals. Its is crunchy on outside and soft on inside. This delicious khoya stuffed dish is mouth watering and loved by all...

info.name: Chena Kheer
info.description: Serves 1 | Chhena kheer is a sweet dish originally from coastal odisha in eastern india. Kheer can have an end number of variations, and chena kheer is one of them. For people who have sweet tooth and swear by desserts made of milk products, this recipe is just perfect. Make it on a special occasion or just to satiate that sugar craving...

info.name: Malai Gilory
info.description: Serves 1 | Malai gilory is an indian sweet where chena slices are stuffed with a rich and flavorful stuffing of milk fudge along with dry fruits and then dunked in thin reduced milk...

info.name: Mewa Gujhiya (Piece)
info.description: Serves 1 | Mewa kesar gujiya is a sweetened deep-fried in ghee moon shaped dumpling made using refined flour (maida) and semolina (suji). Stuffed with khoya (milk solids), cardamom and some nuts (dry fruits) with topping of saffron (kesar). The mithaas of the gujiyas come through from the chaashni (thickened sugar water). The sweetness of these gujias is extremely balanced and doesnt overpower the flavor of the mild nutty, sweetness of the filling...

info.name: Nariyal Laddoo (Piece)
info.description: Serves 1 | Coconut laddoo are traditional indian sweet made with desiccated coconut, cardamom powder, a sweetener & milk acting for moist and sweetness. Coconut laddoo is not just astoundingly delicious, it is also healthy. Coconut contains a considerable amount of minerals like manganese, copper and iron that takes care of our immune system and strengthens our bones and muscles.
